						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the shrine, south of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Kāḷahastīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśivadēva-mahārāya. Ś. 1489: 1567 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The details of date given in the record, viz., Śaka 1489, Prabhava, Dhanus, śu 9, Monday corresponds to 1567 A.D., December 10, Wednesday (not Monday). This inscription is very badly damaged and nothing can be made out beyond the date.</p>						

						</summary>
